title: 3 Slot Payphone Coin Box
desc: This is an original 3 slot payphone coin box with self locking lid.  This type was used in Gray, Automatic Electric, Western Electric and Northern Electric payphones.  If you phone is missing the top rail that opens and closes the top I have some available.  This box pictured is not necessarily the one you will receive, you will get one that is similar to it.  Not many left!

title: 3 slot payphone key
desc: Western Electric & Automatic Electric 3 slot payphone upper housing key.  One will fit both the WE 10G & 10H locks, the other will fit Automatic Electric 29S locks.  Please specify what type phone you have. Shipping will be $7, USPS Priority Mail for any quantity purchased.

title: AE 40  (1940)
desc: Automatic Electric Monophone or AE 40.  The body and handset are "Bakelite".  The cords and phone number card are original.  The phone is fully functional.  The original rotary dial works.  The original "bell" ringer works on incoming calls.  The phone is in beautiful original condition.

title: Early Repro Instruction Card
desc: This is a reproduction of a very early 3 slot payphone card.  I used this same one on a couple of my very early phones.

title: Gray WE 50-G 3
desc: Real Gray/Western Electric 50G payphone. See my Gray/Western Electric 50G for more details.

title: NOS Western Electric Lock with 2 Keys
desc: NOS Medico lock with 2 keys for Western Electric payphones.  This lock was made for the upper housing and the vault of Western Electric single slot payphones.  It can be used with slight modification on the vault doors of both Western Electric and Northern Electric 3 slot payphones.  These locks were found in storage where they were forgotten back in the 1990s.  Save on shipping costs by purchasing several at the same time.

title: Payphone, Works As a Regular Phone
desc: I have real working Western Electric single slot payphones that can work as a regular phone in your home, office or man cave.  The dial out and receive calls and ring just like a regular telephone.

title: Red White and Blue Orig Instruction Card
desc: This is an original (NOS) instruction card for a 3 slot payphone.  This would go in the card holder below the dial.  Not listed here but I do have some complete card holders available.

title: Single Slot Payphone Coin Box With Lid
desc: New Old Stock coin box with self locking lid for your single slot payphone.  I only have a very limited supply of them.

title: Smart Payphone, Works with coins
desc: I have real Western Electric "smart phones" with Protel chassis in them.  They will plug right into your phone line and work as a payphone would.  Local calls (7 digit) will cost 25 cents, most long distance 50 cents, 911 and 800 numbers are free and don't require the insertion of a coin.  You can also receive calls on it.  It comes with an internal coin box where the coins are collected until you remove them.

title: WE Single Slot out of service sign
desc: From a Bell Company I acquired these back around 1990 these out of order signs are for single slot payphones.  I only have a very limited supply.  They push into the coin slot to stop people from putting money into the phone.
